Troubleshooting SSH
Connection Refused

Check:

systemctl status ssh

and:

ss -tulpn | grep :22
Timeout

Check:

Firewall
Network connectivity
Security groups (cloud)
Routing
Permission Denied

Verify:

~/.ssh/authorized_keys

Check file permissions:

chmod 700 ~/.ssh
chmod 600 ~/.ssh/authorized_keys
Biggest Mistakes Engineers Make
❌ Sharing private keys

Never share:

id_rsa
id_ed25519

Only share the public key.

❌ Enabling root SSH login

Avoid:

PermitRootLogin yes

Use normal users with sudo.

❌ Leaving password authentication enabled

Key-based authentication is safer and preferred in production.

