A junior engineer logs into servers using passwords.

A professional DevOps engineer:

Uses SSH keys.
Uses SSH configs.
Uses rsync.
Disables root login.
Uses least-privilege access.
Secures SSH before exposing a server publicly.

These habits will save you from many production incidents later.

